[The seasonal northern hemisphere influenza virus epidemics are in full swing, more or less according to expectation. The predominant virus is an A(H3N2) virus with distinctive antigenic properties that are poorly matched by the current seasonal vaccine virus. Outside of North America the antigenic properties of the H3N2 epidemic virus remain less clear.

Despite the uncertainties regarding the antigenic specificity of the H3N2 virus in North America, this report suggests that the 2014/15 influenza epidemic has reached its peak. What is clear is that no antigenically novel A-type influenza viruses have appeared and the epidemic virus characterised so far remains predominantly resistant to the neuraminidase-inhibiters currently in wide spread use, suggesting that the clinical use of these antivirals is being carefully controlled. - Mod.CP]
